The summary spreadsheet, which follows this one, shows a data grid with the answers to any questionnaire items you might have included in your test. The format of that grid is shown below. data.name: sTokenExplanation
data.value: Tokens can be used to uniquely identify test takers across sites. You can employ them to uniquely identify a test taker who is redirected to or from an IAT. If you are unsure whether you need a token, leave this box unchecked. Consult the manual for further information.

data.name: sTokenTypesExplanation
data.value: If your IAT uses a token, that token must be passed to your IAT in the query string with the token name you provide below. You will be provided with an example upon the upload of your test. That token will be recorded with the IAT data and visible in result data file. The same token will be passed in the query string to the URL the test taker is redirected to upon completion of your test. Tokens have a much more powerful application detailed in the manual.

This error surfaced while negotiating the transfer of information prior to the transfer itself, during the "handshake" as it is usually known.
